author: sussman
msg: Finish the missing #962 edge-case for 0.17 milestone.  This makes
'rm dir; svn rm dir' not error out.  It also makes the scheduled deletion
committable.  Oh, and a regression test too.
* adm_ops.c (svn_wc_delete):  following up the #863 fix, use the same
test later in the code.  if adm_probe_retrieve returns the parent
baton (which is what already have), then don't attempt to mark any
tree for deletion.
* commit_util.c (harvest_committables):  if a committable directory
can't be recursed into (i.e. can't get an associated lock), then
check to see if it's missing and schedule-delete.  If so, just skip
the recursion and add it to the list of committables.
* svn_error_codes.h (SVN_ERR_WC_PATH_FOUND):  new error code.
* svn_wc.h, entries.c (svn_wc_mark_missing_deleted): new public
function.
* commit.c (svn_client_commit): make sure post-commit processing
doesn't choke either.  if a deleted directory is missing, don't
choke -- just mark it as 'deleted' in the parent using the new wc
function.  [This special-case routine turned out to be *way* less
messy than creating multiple special cases within svn_client_commit
and svn_wc_process_committed.]
* schedule_tests.py (delete_missing):  new regression test.
